        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 8:47PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 842 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of thunderstorms
extending from near Great Falls southeast across the Little Belts
with movement to the northeast at 35 mph. In addition to lightning,
a period of rain and gusty winds to 40 mph are expected with the
arrival of the thunderstorms.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph in addition to lightning and a
period of rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...!Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Benton, Stanford, Belt, Hobson, Geyser, Highwood, Carter,
Floweree, Raynesford, Windham, Moccasin, Portage, Sapphire Village,
Ackley Lake State Park, Utica, Shonkin, Armington, Buffalo, and
Benchland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
